observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management is amenable to:
Require the concerned LGU officers and inventory committee to finish conducting the annual physical count of PPEs, which also includes the Road Network System following the required format prescribed in COA Circular 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015;
Require the Accounting Office and the Property Custodian to reconcile their respective records regularly for check and balance;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to prepare adjusting entries on the unrecorded ICT Equipment and misclassified air-conditioning Units;
Require the Property Custodian to render a (a) Report on Local Road Network at the end of each accounting period; (b) Local Road Inventory and Road map; and (c) Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and their components; and
Prioritize and commit to conducting the cleansing of the PPE account balance in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006, dated January 31, 2020.

We recommended and the Management agreed the following: 

Require the concerned LGU officers and inventory committee to conduct the annual physical count of PPEs that includes the Road Network System following the required format prescribed in COA Circular 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015;

Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain the subsidiary ledger cards for each group of PPEs.

Require the General Services Officer to render a (a) Report on Local Road Network at the end of each accounting period (b) Local Road Inventory and Road Map (c) Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components.

Require the Municipal Engineer to assess and evaluate the projects recorded in the Road Networks account and provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO (Local Treasurer, in the absence of GSO) a complete and detailed description and cost segregation of the road components indicating specific measurements of the surface type, maintenance cost, initial costs incurred or valuation, date of completion, location and other necessary data;

Require the Municipal Accountant and the GSO (Local Treasurer, in the absence of GSO) to reconcile its Road Network records in order to present an accurate, reliable, complete and accurate valuation of the Road Network account.

