We ardently recommend that management prioritize / commit to undertaking the cleansing of the PPE account balance pursuant to COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020.

We recommended that Management:
Require the Municipal Development Council and the budget committee to judiciously plan and identify the Programs/Projects/Activities (PPAs) to be funded out of the 20% Development Fund and include only those that are feasible and could be accomplished within the target date of completion;
Fully implement the programmed development PPAs during the year as embodied in the Annual Investment/Development Plan and ensure optimum utilization of the 20% Development Fund for the benefit of the constituents of the Municipality;
Promptly implement all the PPAs under the continuing appropriation;
Strictly observe proper timelines and install effective monitoring of fund utilization and implementation; and
Ensure that all savings from completed projects and all projects that are no longer feasible and not yet implemented are considered for immediate realignment subject to budgetary rules or reverted back to the unappropriated surplus of the 20% Development Fund for re-appropriation to other development projects.

We recommended and the Management agreed the following:

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to eliminate reciprocal accounts for purposes of consolidation of the funds maintained by the LGU in order to reflect the actual receivable and payable of the Municipality; furnish COA with a copy of the revised Consolidated Financial statements, together with the eliminating entries made;

Likewise, instruct the Municipal Accountant to make a detailed review of the accounts and determine the cause of the unreconciled amounts and make necessary adjustments/ corrections in the books of accounts to present the correct balances.

We recommended and the Management agreed the following:

Conduct physical count on the donated supplies and to record the donation accordingly;

Implement sound system of internal control immediately such as, but limited to the following:
use of Inspection and Acceptance Report;
use of Requisition Issue Slip;
designate a warehouse custodian;
separate living quarter of the caretakers; and
other precautionary measures deemed necessary such as the use of CCTV in and around the warehouse.

We recommended that Management:

Direct the Municipal Assessor and/or the Municipal Treasurer to exhaust all possible means to secure the TCTs/OCTs of the LGUs land properties as soon as possible as provided under Section 39(2) PD 1445 and Section 148 of COA Circular 92-386;

Direct the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to prepare and maintain Property, Plant and Ledger Card (PPELC), respectively, for each category of property, plant and equipment and to coordinate with each other on a monthly basis to reconcile the records of both offices;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain subsidiary ledgers on each category of PPE to support its balances reflected in the financial statements;

Provide/ establish an archival system to ensure the safety and protection of all government property, public documents or records such as property inventory report, land ownership, and such other records or documents of public interest in the various offices and departments in the municipality.

